When you're in intense editing mode, it would be great to have a small portlet underneath the "Page operations" is a list of recently edited pages. I find that I often want to to-and-fro between pages I've recently edited in a space. The navigation to do this often involves multiple tabs in firefox, but a more formal feature would probably be better.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Server*. Using *Confluence Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFCLOUD-2120].
  {panel}

The {children} macro is nice, showing all children. But as we create larger document structures, we now really need a way to manage the order of child pages. 

We do it now the 'old' way: to include a number as part of the page name. So page name is then something like "1. This page", and "2. That page". However that causes other problems to appear when using more then 9 child pages, as the in current version child pages are ordered using an ASCII sorting algorithme. Page "11. Another page" is listed besides "1. This page".

May be a solution is to have an additional meta-data field on each page in which we can set a integer value, and that is used for sorting. If not filled in (e.g. hided) then fall back on current sorting.

I have two processes a server and a client. Active MQ runs in the server process. The client sends a request to the server with a temporary queue and waits for answer. When the server creates a sender for the temporary queue it blocks and waits for ever.


Server code:
============
import javax.jms.ExceptionListener;
import javax.jms.JMSException;
import javax.jms.Message;
import javax.jms.MessageListener;
import javax.jms.Queue;
import javax.jms.QueueConnection;
import javax.jms.QueueConnectionFactory;
import javax.jms.QueueReceiver;
import javax.jms.QueueSender;
import javax.jms.QueueSession;
import javax.jms.Session;
import javax.jms.TextMessage;
import org.codehaus.activemq.ActiveMQConnection;
import org.codehaus.activemq.ActiveMQConnectionFactory;
import org.codehaus.activemq.broker.BrokerConnector;
import org.codehaus.activemq.broker.impl.BrokerConnectorImpl;
import org.codehaus.activemq.broker.impl.BrokerContainerImpl;
import org.codehaus.activemq.message.DefaultWireFormat;
import com.ifbs.logging.Log;

public class Server implements MessageListener, ExceptionListener {
    private final String url = ActiveMQConnection.DEFAULT_URL;
    private final BrokerContainerImpl container;
    private final BrokerConnector brokerConnector;
    private final QueueConnectionFactory factory;
    private final QueueConnection connection;
    private final QueueSession session;
    private final Queue queue;
    private final QueueReceiver receiver;
    private boolean finished = false;

    private Server() throws Exception {
        Log.info(getClass().getName() + " started");
        container = new BrokerContainerImpl(url);
        brokerConnector = new BrokerConnectorImpl(container, url, new DefaultWireFormat());
        container.start();
        brokerConnector.start();
        factory = new ActiveMQConnectionFactory();
        connection = factory.createQueueConnection();
        session = connection.createQueueSession(false, Session.AUTO_ACKNOWLEDGE);
        queue = session.createQueue("CopeServer");
        receiver = session.createReceiver(queue);
        connection.setExceptionListener(this);
        receiver.setMessageListener(this);
        connection.start();
    }

    public void onMessage(Message msg) {
        try {
            if (msg instanceof TextMessage) {
                String text = ((TextMessage) msg).getText();
                Log.info("Message received: " + text);
                TextMessage replayMessage = session.createTextMessage("*** " + text + " ***");
                Queue replayQueue = (Queue) msg.getJMSReplyTo();
                if (replayQueue == null) {
                    throw new NullPointerException("Replay queue must not be null");
                }
                QueueSession replaySession = connection.createQueueSession(false, Session.AUTO_ACKNOWLEDGE);
                Log.info("Create sender");
                QueueSender sender = replaySession.createSender(replayQueue);  // Hangig call !!!
                Log.info("Send replay message");
                sender.send(replayMessage);
                Log.info("Message sent");
            }
        } catch (Exception e) {
            Log.error(e);
        } finally {
            wakeup();
        }
    }

    public void onException(JMSException e) {
        Log.error("Handle exception");
        Log.error(e);
    }

    private synchronized void sleep() throws InterruptedException {
        if (!finished) {
            wait();
        }
    }

    private synchronized void wakeup() {
        finished = true;
        notify();
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        try {
            Server server = new Server();
            server.sleep();
        } catch (Exception e) {
            Log.error(e);
        }
    }
}


